Package org.sopra.api.exercises.exercise2

Interface Quicksort<T>

public interface Quicksort<T>
This interface models a quick sort algorithm for arrays of type <Quicksort>.

  • Method Summary

    Modifier and Type Method Description
    int partition​(T[] arr, int left, int right)
    This function takes the middle element as pivot and places all smaller (smaller than pivot) to left of pivot and all greater elements to right of pivot.
    void quicksort​(T[] arr, int left, int right)
    This function sorts a given (unsorted) array by a quick sort algorithm within given left & right border.

  • Method Details

    • partition

      int partition​(T[] arr, int left, int right)
      This function takes the middle element as pivot and places all smaller (smaller than pivot) to left of pivot and all greater elements to right of pivot.
      Parameters:
      arr - Array of unsorted elements <Quicksort>
      left - Left border for current iteration
      right - Right border for current iteration
      Returns:
      New index AFTER current iteration for next iteration

    • quicksort

      void quicksort​(T[] arr, int left, int right)
      This function sorts a given (unsorted) array by a quick sort algorithm within given left & right border. The array outside that borders stays untouched.
      Parameters:
      arr - Array of unsorted Elements <Quicksort>
      left - left border for iteration
      right - right border for iteration
